Isaac Anumihe, Abuja Presidential candidate of Accord Party, Reverend Isaac Ositelu, has called for a thorough investigation on the circumstances surrounding the crashed helicopter which conveyed the Vice President,  Professor Yemi Osinbajo, to Kogi State, last Saturday. Ositelu asked why government hired a helicopter when the country has a number of aeroplanes made up of jets and helicopters in the presidential fleet being managed by the Nigerian Air force (NAF). He also demanded that the result of the investigation be made public. 